description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This Vacancy &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are offering an exciting opportunity for a pharmacy technician role as system manager for the trust chemotherapy e-prescribing system (Chemocare). Sheffield Teaching Hospitals is the host for the regional chemotherapy e-prescribing system used by 5 trusts within the South Yorkshire and North Derbyshire region.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The system manager will work alongside the advanced specialist pharmacist for chemotherapy e-prescribing to develop and manage the system maintaining expected standards for its use. The system manager will also provide training and support to system users and regional superusers, and will provide links with IT departments in the region.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Us&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The pharmacy department at Sheffield Teaching Hospitals NHS Foundation Trust comprises of approximately 450 staff working across 5 sites delivering care to patients from all over the country. A forward thinking department, we are keen to appoint enthusiastic, knowledgeable and exceptional individuals to help us continue to provide a first class service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who we are looking for&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As systems manager for chemotherapy e-prescribing you will be expected to have experience of electronic prescribing systems, including knowledge and technical skills related to their use. You will be required to have excellent interpersonal skills, be highly motivated, with the ability to work independently and as part of a wider team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you can expect from Sheffield Teaching Hospital NHS Foundation Trust&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be working for an organisation which values and respects all of its staff and the community it serves. The Trust is a leader in the NHS and research sectors and provides excellent benefits for its staff. This includes commitments to professional development but also many policies to support employees in balancing their personal and professional lives.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please see the attached documents to the NHS Jobs page for this vacancy which gives you more detail on why you should come and work for us.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sian Thiagarajah&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Principal Pharmacist Haematology &amp; ATMP&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Email: sian.thiagarajah@nhs.net&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Telephone: 0114 271 2274&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Graham Marsh&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Pharmacy Operations Manager &amp; Deputy Chief Pharmacist&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Email: graham.marsh1@nhs.net&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Telephone: 0114 2266425 / 0114 271264&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As part of the recruitment process at application stage, Sheffield Teaching Hospitals will assess applicants’ individual values and behaviours to ensure that these behaviours align with our PROUD values: Patient First, Respectful, Ownership, Unity and Deliver.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our values are what help to make us different and ‘a Brilliant Place to Work’. We expect all our employees to share our values and demonstrate them in every aspect of their role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be required to undertake an online values assessment at application stage and the results of this assessment will be used as part of the on-going selection process to assess your suitability for the post.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The deadline for completing the online assessment is midnight 16/11/2020.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The link to the assessment can be found below, the address can be copied and pasted into a search engine e.g. google:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; login.talentqgroup.com/Login/SelfService/DRSZXBTMNV&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you have any queries, require any assistance to complete this assessment or have already completed it within the past 12 months, please contact the Trust Recruitment Team at &lt;strong&gt;sth.centralrecruitment@nhs.net&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
